"De Toffol S., Engelhard C., Rauch W.","Influence of climate change on the water resources in an alpine region",2008,"Water Science and Technology","58","4",,"839","846",,,10.2166/wst.2008.705,"http://www.scopus.com/inward/record.url?eid=2-s2.0-53549101328&partnerID=40&md5=85c81e3b01759546823f75f8be40c349","Unit of Environmental Engineering, University of Innsbruck, Technikerstr. 13, 6020 Innsbruck, Austria","De Toffol, S., Unit of Environmental Engineering, University of Innsbruck, Technikerstr. 13, 6020 Innsbruck, Austria; Engelhard, C., Unit of Environmental Engineering, University of Innsbruck, Technikerstr. 13, 6020 Innsbruck, Austria; Rauch, W., Unit of Environmental Engineering, University of Innsbruck, Technikerstr. 13, 6020 Innsbruck, Austria","It is widely accepted that the global warming will impact on water resources. This study investigates the possible influence of climate change on the water resources in an alpine region. A description of the actual situation with emphasis on the water resources from the one side and on the water consuming factors, here called stressors, is given. The probable effects of climate change in the region and their influence on its water resources are then described. The main outcome is that in the analysed region the climate change will rather have positive influence on the water balance by inducing higher precipitations during the rivers' natural low flow period (winter). This outcome contradicts many common predictions, however, this due to the specifics induced by the alpine nature of the catchment. © IWA Publishing 2008.","Alpine region; Climate change; Water resources","drinking water; agriculture; article; catchment; climate; fluid intake; greenhouse effect; hydrology; livestock; precipitation; water analysis; winter; Austria; Climate; Conservation of Natural Resources; Geography; Greenhouse Effect; Water Movements; Water Supply",,,,,,"ATV-DVWK-A 198 2003 Vereinheitlichung und Herleitung von Bemessungswerten für Abwasseranlagen. ATV-DVWK Deutsche Vereinigung fur Wasserwirtschaft, Abwasser und Abfall e.V. HennefCIRCA 2005 Final Report - WFD implementation - Water bodies characterisation - Austrian national report; Eybl, J., Godina, R., Lalk, P., Lorenz, P., Miiller, G. & Weilguni, V. 2005 Das Trockenjahr 2003. In: Mitteilungsblatt des Hydrographischen Dienstes in Österreich Nr. 83Frei, C., Calanca, P., Schar, C., Wanner, H., Schadler, B., Haeberli, W., Appenzeller, C., Hohmann, R., (2007) Klimadnderung und die Schweiz 2050. Erwartete Auswirkungen auf Umwelt, Gesellschaft und Wirtschaft. Grundlagen; Wien, I.W.H.W., (2005) Hydrologischer Atlas Österreichs, HAÖ, , Bundesministerium für Land-und Forstwirtschaft, Umwelt und Wasserwirtschaft; Jrc, (2008) ECALP Data, , European Commission-DG Joint Research Centre Institute for Environment and Sustainability; Kuhn, M., Die Reaktion der österreichisachen Gletscher und ihres Abflusses auf Änderungen von Temperatur und Niederschlag (2004) Österreichische Wasser-und Abfallwirtschaft, 56, pp. 1-7. , Heftl-2; Kuhn, M., Lambrecht, A., Glacier change in the 20th century (2007) Hydrologischer Atlas Österreichs, HAÖ, 3. , Lieferung Bundesministerium für Land-und Forstwirtschaft, Umwelt und Wasserwirtschaft; Laaha, G., Blöschl, G., A comparison of low flow regionalisation methods-catchment grouping (2006) J. Hydrol, 323 (1-4), pp. 193-214; Lambrecht, A., Kuhn, M., Glacier changes in the Austrian Alps during the last three decades, derived from the new Austrian glacier inventory (2007) Ann. Glaciol, 46; LfL Bayerische Landesanstalt für Landwirtschaft 2006 Gruber Tabelle zur Fütterung der Milchkühe, Zuchtrinder, Mastrinder, Schafe, ZiegenSolomon, S., Qin, D., Manning, M., Chen, Z., Marquis, M., Averyt, K. B., Tignor, M. & Miller, H. L. 2007 Climate change 2007 : The Physical Science Basis. (IPCC report). Cambridge, UK and New York, USAAustria, S., Regionalstatistik auf der Basis von geographischen Rastern (2001) Daten aus der Großzählung 2001","De T